cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CV 

This paper is about improving the quality of neural machine translation systems through post-editing and online learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and machine translation. The paper also proposes a new optimization algorithm, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of online learning techniques involves updating the model in real-time, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the reduction of effort required for post-editing, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer vision (cs.CV) tasks that involve large amounts of data.
